19#include "ByteArray.h"
20#include "DecodeStatus.h"
21#include "ZXContainerAlgorithms.h"
22
23#include <memory>
24#include <list>
25#include <string>
26#include <utility>
27
28namespace ZXing {
29
30class CustomData;
31
32/**
33* <p>Encapsulates the result of decoding a matrix of bits. This typically
34* applies to 2D barcode formats. For now it contains the raw bytes obtained,
35* as well as a string interpretation of those bytes, if applicable.</p>
36*
37* @author Sean Owen
38*/
39class DecoderResult
40{
41 DecodeStatus _status = DecodeStatus::NoError;
42 ByteArray _rawBytes;
43 int _numBits = 0;
44 std::wstring _text;
45 std::list<ByteArray> _byteSegments;
46 std::wstring _ecLevel;
47 int _errorsCorrected = -1;
48 int _erasures = -1;
49 int _structuredAppendSequenceNumber = 0;
50 int _structuredAppendCodeCount = 0;
51 int _structuredAppendParity = 0;
52 std::shared_ptr<CustomData> _extra;
53
54 DecoderResult(const DecoderResult &) = delete;
55 DecoderResult& operator=(const DecoderResult &) = delete;
56
57public:
58 DecoderResult(DecodeStatus status) : _status(status) {}
59 DecoderResult(ByteArray&& rawBytes, std::wstring&& text) : _rawBytes(std::move(rawBytes)), _text(std::move(text)) {
60 _numBits = 8 * Size(_rawBytes);
61 }
62
63 DecoderResult() = default;
64 DecoderResult(DecoderResult&&) = default;
65 DecoderResult& operator=(DecoderResult&&) = default;
66
67 bool isValid() const { return StatusIsOK(_status); }
68 DecodeStatus errorCode() const { return _status; }
69
70 const ByteArray& rawBytes() const & { return _rawBytes; }
71 ByteArray&& rawBytes() && { return std::move(_rawBytes); }
72 const std::wstring& text() const & { return _text; }
73 std::wstring&& text() && { return std::move(_text); }
74
75 // Simple macro to set up getter/setter methods that save lots of boilerplate.
76 // It sets up a standard 'const & () const', 2 setters for setting lvalues via
77 // copy and 2 for setting rvalues via move. They are provided each to work
78 // either on lvalues (normal 'void (...)') or on rvalues (returning '*this' as
79 // rvalue). The latter can be used to optionally initialize a temporary in a
80 // return statement, e.g.
81 // return DecoderResult(bytes, text).setEcLevel(level);
82#define ZX_PROPERTY(TYPE, GETTER, SETTER) \
83 const TYPE& GETTER() const & { return _##GETTER; } \
84 TYPE&& GETTER() && { return std::move(_##GETTER); } \
85 void SETTER(const TYPE& v) & { _##GETTER = v; } \
86 void SETTER(TYPE&& v) & { _##GETTER = std::move(v); } \
87 DecoderResult&& SETTER(const TYPE& v) && { _##GETTER = v; return std::move(*this); } \
88 DecoderResult&& SETTER(TYPE&& v) && { _##GETTER = std::move(v); return std::move(*this); }
89
90 ZX_PROPERTY(int, numBits, setNumBits)
91 ZX_PROPERTY(std::list<ByteArray>, byteSegments, setByteSegments)
92 ZX_PROPERTY(std::wstring, ecLevel, setEcLevel)
93 ZX_PROPERTY(int, errorsCorrected, setErrorsCorrected)
94 ZX_PROPERTY(int, erasures, setErasures)
95 ZX_PROPERTY(int, structuredAppendParity, setStructuredAppendParity)
96 ZX_PROPERTY(int, structuredAppendSequenceNumber, setStructuredAppendSequenceNumber)
97 ZX_PROPERTY(int, structuredAppendCodeCount, setStructuredAppendCodeCount)
98 ZX_PROPERTY(std::shared_ptr<CustomData>, extra, setExtra)
99
100#undef ZX_PROPERTY
101
102 bool hasStructuredAppend() const { return _structuredAppendParity >= 0 && _structuredAppendSequenceNumber >= 0; }
103};
104
105} // ZXing
